structures.dict

Interface Dict<K,V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedDict, OpenAddressingDict

    public interface Dict<K,V>
extends java.io.Serializable
    List of pairs. Dictionary is a data structure which allows to save data in a key-value format. This is an alternative to linear data structures, such as array or vector, in which a numeric key is necessary. Instead, any type of class might be used as a key.

    Dictionary complexity tends to 1, but it gets bigger as the array begins to fill. In order to retrieve good complexity, a resize of the array is done whenever the number of pairs against the array capacity overflows a factor.

    This class is a member of the HarambeDB database framework.

    • Method Detail

      • add

        void add(K key,
         V value)
        Adds a pair of key-value to the list. The key gets hashed and properly added into position. If the given key already exists, the previous value gets overrided with the new one.
        Parameters:
        key - key of the pair
        value - value of the pair

      • remove

        V remove(K key)
        Removes a pair of key-value with given key and returns the previous value. If the given key does not exist, it returns null. Removin the value also removes the key and decrements the size.
        Parameters:
        key - key of the pair to be removed
        Returns:
        previous value of the pair or null if pair does not exist

      • getValue

        V getValue(K key)
        Hashes the key and returns the corresponding value. If said value does not exists, it returns null.
        Parameters:
        key - key of the pair to be found
        Returns:
        value of the given pair

      • contains

        boolean contains(K key)
        Checks if the dictionary contains a pair with given key. It returns true if there exists a pair with given key, false if not.
        Parameters:
        key - key for the pair to be found
        Returns:
        true if key exists, false if not
